com.vijfhart.casus.tree

Class WrapperNode<T extends WrapperNode<T,E>,E extends java.lang.Comparable<E>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.vijfhart.casus.tree.AbstractNode<T>
      • com.vijfhart.casus.tree.WrapperNode<T,E>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    LevelComparable<T>, Node<T>, java.lang.Comparable<T>

    public abstract class WrapperNode<T extends WrapperNode<T,E>,E extends java.lang.Comparable<E>>
extends AbstractNode<T>
    A Wrapper class to create a Tree-node out of any Comparable object. A WrapperNode is a subclass of AbstractNode. It keeps a reference to the contained object.

        public int compareTo(T other)
        Overridden version of compareTo to implement Comparable. This method is implemented in the same way as in AbstractNode, with the following added behavior: sibblings are ordered by using the compareTo method of the wrapped object.
